# Cap - Core & C# Architecture

## Architecture
- `src/Core/`: pure C# (.NET 8), zero Godot — no `using Godot;`, no Node/Resource inheritance, no Godot math.
- `src/Godot/CoreBridge/`: ONLY Godot-side C# — autoloads (`GodotTickDriver`) and `[GlobalClass]` handles (`SimulationMachineHandle`) so GDScript can drive Core without referencing Core assemblies directly.
- Core runs factory simulation state; Godot interprets and renders it.
- **Grid positions**: simple integer structures (X, Y, Z) in Core for simulation indexing — no float drift.

## Core Mechanics
- Fixed tick loop via `SimulationClock` + `ITickable`; Godot frame delta accumulates into ticks in `GodotTickDriver`.
- Entities, recipes, and items live under `src/Core/Data/` and `src/Core/Simulation/`.
- No background world-gen queues, `ArrayPool` chunk tiles, or noise unless explicitly requested.

## C# Style
- File-scoped namespaces; primary constructors / records where they fit.
- PascalCase types/methods/properties; camelCase arguments/locals; `_camelCase` private fields.
- Node retrieval: use `[Export]` for structural scene wiring instead of loose string-path `GetNode()` calls.
